{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771580122,"nonce":"JJA3Ixgqd/RRamb4rVJDDq6WObQ=","title":"Replace auto-dismissing toasts with persistent in-context error messages","message":"Flash messages are rendered as toasts (lower right corner) that auto-dismiss after a few seconds. This is an accessibility problem and a dark pattern:\n\n- Users who don't notice the toast miss error feedback entirely\n- Errors require persistent, in-context display so users understand what went wrong\n- Success messages as toasts are acceptable, but errors should not disappear\n\nProposed approach:\n- Error/alert flash messages should be rendered inline near the action that caused them (e.g. inside the modal, above the form, next to the button)\n- Success/notice messages can remain as toasts\n- Consider WCAG guidelines for error feedback\n\nFound during Phase C integration testing. Not in scope for Phase C.","files":null}]}